publicationXrefa9b.standardName: Simultaneous induction of autophagy and toll-like receptor signaling pathways by graphene oxide.

pathway.author: [Egonw, Eweitz]

comments.content: Graphene oxide has been found in the RAW264.7 to trigger a cytokine response and resulting autophagy. It was found to be mediated by  activation of TLR4 and TLR9, signalling MyD88, TRAF6, and NF-B, resulting in cytokine expression. However, TLR signaling did not cause IFN- expression nor IRF3 activation. The process also shows activation of Beclin 1 and LC3.
